casebody.data:
Levy, Appellant, v. Kohn, Respondent. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. June 26, 1890.) Appeal from seventh district court.

Argued before Allen, P. J., and Bookstaver, J.

Fromme Bros., for appellant. O. Cohen, for respondent.

Ho opinion. Judgment reversed, with costs to plaintiff (appellant) to abide the event. Order of interpleader vacated, and proceedings remitted to district court.
